name: blspy
documentation_summary: The HTML text provides information about "blspy," a Python package available on PyPI (Python Package Index) for implementing BLS (Boneh-Lynn-Shacham) signatures with Python bindings to C++. The latest version, 2.0.2, was released on June 26, 2023. It includes features like non-interactive signature aggregation according to the IETF BLS RFC, efficient verification using Proof of Possession, key and signature serialization, and support for EIP-2333 key derivation. The package requires Python version 3.7 or higher and is maintained by the Chia Network. The project description emphasizes that the library has not been formally reviewed for security and has shifted to the IETF BLS specification as of July 16, 2020. The documentation also includes instructions for creating keys and signatures, serializing them, and verifying signatures, along with notes on building the library, contributing guidelines, and licensing information.
